name: Boomerang
oracle_text: Return target permanent to its owner's hand.
flavor_text: Early Jamuraan hunters devised a weapon that would return to its source. Tolarian Æthermancers developed a spell that skipped the weapon entirely.

name: Cancel
oracle_text: Counter target spell.

name: Cinder Pyromancer
oracle_text:
{T}: Cinder Pyromancer deals 1 damage to target player or planeswalker.
Whenever you cast a red spell, you may untap Cinder Pyromancer.
flavor_text: "If the whole world burns, I'll never grow cold."

name: Civic Wayfinder
oracle_text: When Civic Wayfinder enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic land card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
flavor_text: "These alleys are not safe. Come, I can guide you back to the market square."

name: Cloud Sprite
oracle_text:
Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
Cloud Sprite can block only creatures with flying.
flavor_text: The delicate sprites carry messages for Saprazzans, but they refuse to land in Mercadia City's filthy markets.

name: Drudge Skeletons
oracle_text: {B}: Regenerate Drudge Skeletons. (The next time this creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)
flavor_text:
"The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, never surrender, and don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."
—Nevinyrral, *Necromancer's Handbook*

name: Dusk Imp
oracle_text: Flying
flavor_text: Imps are just intelligent enough to have an understanding of cruelty.

name: Elvish Eulogist
oracle_text: Sacrifice Elvish Eulogist: You gain 1 life for each Elf card in your graveyard.
flavor_text: "No matter how adept our artistic skill, our effigies can never hope to capture the vibrant beauty of a living elf. Perhaps that is truly why we mourn."

name: Elvish Visionary
oracle_text: When Elvish Visionary enters the battlefield, draw a card.
flavor_text: Before any major undertaking, a Cylian elf seeks the guidance of a visionary to learn the will of the gargantuan ancients.

name: Elvish Warrior
flavor_text: As graceful as a deer leaping a stream and as deadly as the wolf waiting in ambush on the other side, elvish warriors are the eyes of the forest as well as its unsheathed claws.

name: Essence Drain
oracle_text: Essence Drain deals 3 damage to any target and you gain 3 life.
flavor_text:
"The elves are right: Death inevitably leads to life. But the truly powerful don't just experience this cycle. They control it."
—Crovax, ascendant evincar

name: Essence Scatter
oracle_text: Counter target creature spell.
flavor_text: Some wizards compete not to summon the most interesting creatures, but to create the most interesting aftereffects when a summons goes awry.

name: Eyeblight's Ending
oracle_text: Destroy target non-Elf creature.
flavor_text:
"Those without beauty are Lorwyn's greatest tumor. The winnowers have an unpleasant duty, but a necessary one."
—Eidren, perfect of Lys Alana

name: Giant Growth
oracle_text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Giant Spider
oracle_text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor_text: The giant spider's silk naturally resists gravity, almost weaving itself as it blankets the forest canopy.

name: Goblin Piker
flavor_text: Once he'd worked out which end of the thing was sharp, he was promoted to guard duty.

name: Goblin Sky Raider
oracle_text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor_text: The goblin word for "flying" is more accurately translated as "falling slowly."

name: Hill Giant
flavor_text: Fortunately, hill giants have large blind spots in which a human can easily hide. Unfortunately, these blind spots are beneath the bottoms of their feet.

name: Incinerate
oracle_text: Incinerate deals 3 damage to any target. A creature dealt damage this way can't be regenerated this turn.
flavor_text:
"Yes, I think 'toast' is an appropriate description."
—Jaya Ballard, task mage

name: Lightning Elemental
oracle_text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor_text:
"A flash of the lightning, a break of the wave, He passes from life to his rest in the grave."
—William Knox, "Mortality"

name: Lys Alana Huntmaster
oracle_text: Whenever you cast an Elf spell, you may create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token.
flavor_text: From the highest tiers of Dawn's Light Palace to the deepest shade of Wren's Run, the silver notes of the horn shimmer through the air, and all who hear it feel its pull.

name: Mind Rot
oracle_text: Target player discards two cards.
flavor_text:
"The beauty of mental attacks is that your victims never remember them."
—Volrath

name: Moonglove Winnower
oracle_text: Deathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
flavor_text: Winnowers live to eliminate eyeblights, creatures the elves deem too ugly to exist.

name: Naturalize
oracle_text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor_text: If you want to destroy something lifeless, make it live.

name: Natural Spring
oracle_text: Target player gains 8 life.
flavor_text:
"Jewels cannot be eaten nor gold drunk. What civilization trades, nature simply provides."
—Molimo, maro-sorcerer

name: Negate
oracle_text: Counter target noncreature spell.
flavor_text: Masters of the arcane savor a delicious irony. Their study of deep and complex arcana leads to such a simple end: the ability to say merely yes or no.

name: Rampant Growth
oracle_text: Search your library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
flavor_text: Nature grows solutions to its problems.

name: Ravenous Rats
oracle_text: When Ravenous Rats enters the battlefield, target opponent discards a card.
flavor_text: Nothing is sacred to rats. Everything is simply another meal.

name: Runeclaw Bear
flavor_text: Bears aren't always as strong and as mean as you imagine. Some are even stronger and meaner.

name: Severed Legion
oracle_text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)
flavor_text: No one in Aphetto answers a knock at the door after sundown.

name: Shock
oracle_text: Shock deals 2 damage to any target.
flavor_text:
"Once I saw a goblin shouting at a thunderstorm. He lost the argument pretty quickly."
—Wandering mage

name: Snapping Drake
oracle_text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor_text: Foul-tempered, poorly trained, and mule-stubborn, the drake is the perfect test of the master's will.

name: Spined Wurm
flavor_text: Its spines act like the teeth of a saw, scoring distinctive marks in the vegetation of its territory.

name: Terror
oracle_text: Destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.

name: Trained Armodon
flavor_text: Armodons are trained to step on things. Enemy things.

name: Unholy Strength
oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +2/+1.
flavor_text:
"Born under the moon, the second child will stumble on temptation and seek power in the dark places of the heart."
—Codex of the Constellari

name: Unsummon
oracle_text: Return target creature to its owner's hand.
flavor_text: Mages routinely summon creatures from the Æther. It's only fair that they occasionally throw one back.

name: Wall of Spears
oracle_text:
Defender (This creature can't attack.)
First strike
flavor_text:
"A stick is your friend. A pointed stick is your good friend. An army of pointed sticks is your best friend."
—Onean sergeant

name: Wall of Wood
oracle_text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)
flavor_text: Orcish lumberjacks spent the night sharpening their blades and resting for a day of labor. They awoke to find that the forest had been making its own preparations.
